modules.description: Provides AES, RSA, and elliptic curve operations with built-in resistance to timing attacks, including key generation, encryption, and signature verification. Works with byte sequences, big integers, and cryptographic keys. Used for secure communication protocols and data integrity checks in networked applications.

Initializes a Fortuna RNG using system entropy sources, incorporating CPU-based randomness and periodic calls to getrandom(). Operates on a generator type from Mirage_crypto_rng, managing entropy collection and seeding. Used to securely seed cryptographic operations in environments requiring predictable yet random data generation.
